      <TextArea fx:id="textArea" layoutX="105.0" layoutY="162.0" prefHeight="364.0" prefWidth="819.0" text="   RGB - an additive color model that describes a method of color synthesis in which red, green,&#10;and blue light are superimposed together, mixing into different colors. Widely used in the &#10;technique of reproducing images using light radiation.&#10;   The number of gradations of each channel depends on the bit size of the RGB bit value and&#10;therefore the number of gradations is 256, which allows you to encode 2563 = 16 777 216 colors&#10;&#10;Benefits:&#10;  - Hardware proximity to the monitor, scanner, projector, other devices;&#10;  - Large range of colors, close to the capabilities of human vision;&#10;  - Availability of many image processing functions (filters) in raster graphics programs;&#10;  - Small (compared to the CMYK model) volume, but a wider range of colors.&#10;&#10;Negative:&#10;  - Preservation of the probability of error of color display on the monitor screen - &#10;does not correspond to the colors obtained as a result of color testing.&#10;&#10;   HSV - is a color model based on three color characteristics: color tone (Hue), saturation &#10;(Saturation) and color value (Value), which is also called brightness (Brightness).&#10; - Hue - color tone (for example, red, green or blue).&#10; - Saturation - saturation. Varies between 0-100 or 0-1.&#10; - Value - the value of color, or Brightness - brightness. Also set in the range 0-100 or 0-1.&#10;&#10;Benefits:&#10;  - It is convenient to change color brightness, and also to select a color palette;&#10;  - The color model is human-oriented and the parameters describe the properties of colors &#10;in terms of how a person perceives color&#10;&#10;Negative:&#10;  - Сomponents H and V are dependent, ie the main color depends on the intensity&#10;  - Еhe color model is not hardware-oriented and requires conversion to be displayed">
